For some reason the [i]getPlugin()[/i] function is still [i]null[/i] even though I have this:

[code=java]        /**
	 * Creates a new plugin container
	 */
	@SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
	public PluginContainer(String name, int id, boolean active) {
		try {
			Class<Plugin> plugin = (Class<Plugin>) Class.forName(name);

			this.setId(id);
			this.setName(name);
			this.setPlugin(plugin.newInstance());
			this.setStillActive(active);
		} catch (Exception e) {
			e.printStackTrace();
		}
	}[/code]

